<div id="befriend-your-finance-team"></div>
<h3>2. Befriend your finance team</h3>
<p>The typical trope is that marketers and finance teams work against each other. One group is tasked with spending money to get customers, and the other is judged by how judiciously it protects a business&#8217;s bottom line. <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kristinblitch/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Kristin Blitch</a>, director of marketing at <a href="https://rjeinteriors.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RJE Interiors</a>, believes thereâ€™s a better way to approach this relationship.</p>
<p>â€œThis is going to sound silly, but befriend your finance team,â€ she said. â€œOur CFO is one of my closest allies, so I work with the team to see where I can cut expenses and make sensible savings.â€</p>
<p>Kristin added that her partnership with finance makes it easier to try new strategies. &#8220;When I ask to spend money, trust has been built that it&#8217;s not just something on a whim,&#8221; she explained. &#8220;There&#8217;s intentionality and reason behind it. From there, I can make things work and bring new things to the table because we&#8217;ve usually got a plan in place.&#8221;</p>
<p>One constant challenge for marketers is proving the value of our actions to the rest of the team. Having an ally in finance who understands what you do and why you do it would be a big step in alleviating that challenge.</p>
<div id="leverage-your-internal-influencers"></div>
<h3>3. Leverage your internal influencers</h3>
<p>Unless youâ€™re producing big-budget, celebrity-filled commercials, your biggest marketing costs arenâ€™t tied up in the creativeâ€”itâ€™s paying for the distribution channels (like <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/07/18/social-media-advertising">paid social media ads</a>).</p>
<p>Kristin has a solution for that, too. &#8220;I work to have our internal team help us share our communications (especially the important ones) externally to improve reach in conjunction with any boosting or advertising,&#8221; she said.</p>
<p>For example, if youâ€™re launching a new product or starting a new campaign, you could ask your team to post about it on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/generating-leads-on-linkedin">LinkedIn</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-to-stretch-budget-wordstream-RTE-png.webp" alt="Stretch your marketing budget - RJI LinkedIn repost." width="784" height="792" class="aligncenter wp-image-90297 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-to-stretch-budget-wordstream-RTE-png.webp 784w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-to-stretch-budget-wordstream-RTE-480x485.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 784px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Internal influencing can be as easy as asking your team to repost important company updates.</em></p>
<p>Iâ€™ve written about the power of internal influencers before (it was one of the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/2025-marketing-tips">top tips from expert marketers</a> for 2025). Theyâ€™re a fantastic way to expand the reach of your marketing messages without extra ad costs.</p>
<p>Kristin said they can also add a trust layer to your marketing. â€œHaving authenticity and word of mouth from our team to their followers (directly) means more compared to just paying for the clicks.â€</p>
<div id="dont-overspend-on-seasonal-campaigns"></div>
<h3>4. Donâ€™t overspend on a few seasonal campaigns</h3>
<p>As an experienced digital marketing consultant at <a href="http://localiq.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LocaliQ</a>, <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/mkaywood/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Miranda Kaywood</a> gets a behind-the-scenes view of how businesses allocate their marketing budgets. She cautioned against spending most of your advertising dollars on a few seasonal campaigns.</p>
<p>â€œInstead of exhausting your budget all at once, I recommend pacing it out to maintain consistent visibility,â€ she said. â€œConsistency is crucial for building long-term brand recognition, as it requires multiple touchpoints with consumers to create meaningful connections.â€</p>
<p>This is true even for seasonal businesses. Say you run a lawn care service. Many of your competitors will turn marketing on in March as the weather gets warm. If youâ€™ve shared a steady stream of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/winter-content-ideas">helpful content all winter</a>, the people it helped will be more likely to choose you come <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/spring-content-ideas">spring</a>.</p>
<p>And once you get a revenue bump from those successful gambits, compound it by putting some of it back into advertising. â€œInvest in these solutions, and once you see a positive ROI, reinvest the returns back into your marketing strategy through a budget increase or trying out different marketing avenues,â€ Miranda said.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="ğŸ’¡" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Want to keep your growth going?</strong> Download <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/always-on-marketing?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_alwaysonmarketing_Download&amp;itm_source=localiq&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent_links">Always On Marketing: The Not-So-Secret Strategy for Unstoppable Growth</a></p>
<div id="target-2nd-or-3rd-google-ads-positions"></div>
<h3>5. Target second or third Google Ads positions</h3>
<p>The top spot on a Google search results page almost always gets the most clicks. But that real estate comes at a price. <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/adamschwind/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Adam Schwind</a>, founder of <a href="https://sparkdigitalgroup.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Spark Digital Group</a>, believes thereâ€™s gold in not fighting the big spenders for those extra clicks.</p>
<p>â€œRather than competing for the number one spot in <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/how-to-run-google-ads">Google Ads</a>, where costs can be significantly higher, businesses can maximize their budget by targeting the second or third position,â€ he said. â€œThis approach reduces cost per click (CPC) while still maintaining strong visibility and competitive click-through rates (CTR), ensuring a better return on ad spend.â€</p>
<p>I really like this bit of advice. Iâ€™ve watched the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/2024-google-ads-benchmarks">search ad costs</a> we track yearly rise. Just in the last four years, the average cost-per-lead from our benchmark reports jumped by roughly 50%.</p>
<p>Adamâ€™s suggestion is a great option for tempering those cost increases to keep your budget intact.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6d1.png" alt="ğŸ›‘" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><strong> Free budget-saving resource:</strong> <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/ways-to-save-money-in-google-ads?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_SaveMoneyinGoogleAds_Download">6 Easy Ways to Save Money on Google Ads Now</a></p>
<div id="be-ready-to-pivot"></div>
<h3>6. Be ready to pivot</h3>
<p>Experimentation is a constant part of great marketing. Whatâ€™s important, Miranda said, is to make sure youâ€™re not doubling down on the experiments that donâ€™t pan out.</p>
<p>â€œItâ€™s key to regularly check in and see whatâ€™s actually working so you can understand how your marketing dollars are being spent,â€ she explained. â€œYou might discover that some platforms, ads, or audiences perform better than othersâ€”and you need to pivot to make sure youâ€™re always effectively using your dollars.â€</p>
<p>Thatâ€™s true whether you manage your own marketing budgets or have outside help. â€œYour marketing partner (i.e., LocaliQ) can help with this, but itâ€™s important for you to stay on top of it, too,â€ Miranda added.</p>
<p>A great place to start is while creating your yearly <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/01/07/best-marketing-strategies">marketing strategy</a>. Be precise about which metrics matter to you most in the coming year. Set a benchmark based on your industry and on your prior results. Then, establish a cadence for review and be prepared to shift your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ads-budget">budget</a> from whatâ€™s not working to what is.</p>
<div id="be-strategic-with-your-marketing-channels"></div>
<h3>7. Be strategic with your marketing channels</h3>
<p>It can be tempting to jump into a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/06/26/marketing-channels">marketing channel</a> that gets a lot of buzz from other businesses. Adam said that can lead to a leaky marketing budget if itâ€™s not the right channel for your unique brand.</p>
<p>â€œSmall businesses must be strategic about where they invest their marketing budget,â€ Adam explained. He gave the example of a divorce law firm, which may not benefit as much from building a large following on every social channel since â€œdivorce clients seek legal help when needed, not ongoing engagement.â€</p>
<p>Miranda made a similar point. â€œSmall businesses should focus on a few key marketing channels, such as <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2016/03/08/facebook-marketing-ideas">Facebook</a> and Google, rather than trying to cover everything with a limited budget,â€ she said.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/popular-social-media-platforms-logo-4-1024x979.webp" alt="Stretch your marketing budget - chart social media channels." width="1024" height="979" class="aligncenter wp-image-90310 size-large" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/popular-social-media-platforms-logo-4-1024x979.webp 1024w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/popular-social-media-platforms-logo-4-300x287.webp 300w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/popular-social-media-platforms-logo-4-768x734.webp 768w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/popular-social-media-platforms-logo-4-1536x1468.webp 1536w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/popular-social-media-platforms-logo-4-2048x1957.webp 2048w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/popular-social-media-platforms-logo-4-1080x1032.webp 1080w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/popular-social-media-platforms-logo-4-1280x1223.webp 1280w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/popular-social-media-platforms-logo-4-980x937.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/popular-social-media-platforms-logo-4-480x459.webp 480w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Not all channels are ideal for all audiences.</em></p>
<p>Which channels are right for your business?</p>
<p>To answer that youâ€™ll need to know who your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/11/target-audience">most valuable audience</a> is and figure out how they typically learn about brands and services in your industry. Do they actively search certain <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/08/09/easy-keyword-research-guide">keywords</a> on Google? Or do they commonly talk about your topics on a social media platform?</p>
<div id="go-organic"></div>
<h3>8. Go organic</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/colby-flood/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Colby Flood</a>, founder of <a href="https://www.brighterclick.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Brighter Click</a>, is bullish on SEO and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/01/19/social-media-marketing-plan">organic social media</a> for growing brands and has a specific prescription for them to succeed.</p>
<p>â€œSEO is a strategy that takes time and consistency, but the compounding growth it brings is well worth the wait,â€ Colby said. â€œI recommend prioritizing gaining a minimum of 3-5 backlinks and publishing 1-2 <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/07/27/blog-post-ideas">blog articles</a> per month for smaller websites.â€</p>
<p>Weâ€™ve published a guide on getting <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2010/04/01/build-amazing-backlinks">quality backlinks</a> to get you started there.</p>
<p>â€œOrganic content marketing on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/03/19/social-media-for-small-business">social media</a> is another great way to build an audience, but like SEO, it takes time and consistency,â€ Colby added. â€œMany direct-to-consumer (DTC) brands are shifting towards organic social media as a driver for sales.â€</p>
<p>Colby pointed to Fresh Chile Company as a great example of a DTC brand thatâ€™s crushing it on social media. I checked them out, and yeah, a niche product with over 200K followers across Meta platforms is pretty impressive.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-to-stretch-budget-wordstream-chile-1024x661.webp" alt="Stretch your marketing budget - Instagram post from the Fresh Chile Company." width="1024" height="661" class="aligncenter wp-image-90299 size-large" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-to-stretch-budget-wordstream-chile-1024x661.webp 1024w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-to-stretch-budget-wordstream-chile-300x194.webp 300w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-to-stretch-budget-wordstream-chile-768x496.webp 768w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-to-stretch-budget-wordstream-chile-1080x698.webp 1080w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-to-stretch-budget-wordstream-chile-1280x827.webp 1280w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-to-stretch-budget-wordstream-chile-980x633.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-to-stretch-budget-wordstream-chile-480x310.webp 480w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-to-stretch-budget-wordstream-chile-png.webp 1412w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>The Fresh Chile Company&#8217;s Instagram page is a perfect mix of promotion, product ideas, and customer praise.</em></p>
<div id="know-your-customer"></div>
<h3>9. Know your customer</h3>
<p>Both Colby and Kristin told me that knowing your customer is one of the most important steps in getting more from each marketing dollar.</p>
<p>â€œThe single most important aspect of marketing is understanding your customer better than your competitors,â€ Colby said. â€œDo not assume your customers think the same way you do. <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/11/10/best-online-survey-tools">Send out surveys</a>, pick up the phone and call them, dive into <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/reddit-marketing">Reddit threads</a>, do whatever you can to understand the pain points they have relative to your business and how you help solve them.â€</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-to-stretch-budget-wordstream-lawn-png.webp" alt="Stretch your marketing budget - screenshot from Reddit." width="956" height="719" class="alignnone wp-image-90300 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-to-stretch-budget-wordstream-lawn-png.webp 956w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-to-stretch-budget-wordstream-lawn-480x361.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 956px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Reddit is a great place to see what questions your target audience is asking.</em></p>
<p>He offered a systematic approach to the task. â€œWe recommend completing voice of customer and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/competitors-ads">competitor research</a> to better understand the rational and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/05/03/emotional-marketing-copy">emotional motivators</a> that best resonate with your audience,â€ he said. â€œFrom there, weâ€™d select 3-5 motivators to test over a 90-day period. When analyzing ad creative performance, we generally start by looking at the high level to understand how performance averaged based on the messaging motivators, ad format, creative design style, UGC Creator, etc.â€</p>
<p>For Kristin, knowing your customer gives you the freedom to be creative and play a little. â€œKnow your target audience and know how and where to reach them,â€ she said. â€œOnce you know how to reach them, have fun. Itâ€™s scary to make the first video that feels like it might be different, but do it. Having fun is the ultimate way to engage your followers. Once you find something that works, keep tweaking it and having fun.â€</p>
<h2>You donâ€™t have to turn off marketing to stay on budget</h2>
<p>One big takeaway from all of these tips is that you donâ€™t have to stop marketing to <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/local-advertising-costs-in-2025/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">save money on advertising</a>. Actually, keeping a consistent presence on your top channels can help reduce overall costs compared to stopping and starting.</p>
<p>The theme I picked up on was the need to be agile. That means testing to see what works, ditching what doesn&#8217;t, and being ready to shift gears quickly when needed.</p>
