<div id="what-is-a-target-audience"></div>
<h2>What is a target audience?</h2>
<p>Many of the search ads, social ads, commercials, and other marketing promotions that you see are created with the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/11/target-audience">target audience</a> in mind. A target audience is a group of people with shared attributes you intend to reach with your marketing campaign or materials.</p>
<p>Here are the common attributes of a well-defined target audience:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Demographics: </strong>Think age, gender identity, job title, education, location, marital status.</li>
<li><strong>Motivations: </strong>Is the person concerned with personal safety, the environment? Interested in learning new things?</li>
<li><strong>Pain points: </strong>How are their current solutions not working?</li>
<li><strong>Marketing channels: </strong>Do these individuals watch TV, spend time on Facebook, or scroll TikTok? Where can you reach them?</li>
<li><strong>Content preference: </strong>Would they prefer a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/02/09/how-to-write-a-blog-post">blog post</a> or a newsletter? A how-to video or a case study?</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/how-to-find-target-audience.webp" alt="questions to ask to identify target audience" width="936" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-89132" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/how-to-find-target-audience.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/how-to-find-target-audience-480x308.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Figuring out these details will help you fill out a specific target audienceâ€”which will help make your marketing stronger.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f575-fe0f-200d-2640-fe0f.png" alt="ğŸ•µï¸â€â™€ï¸" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Want to know exactly who you should be targeting with your marketing?</strong> Download the guide &gt;&gt; <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteTargetAudience.html?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_TargetAudineceGuide_Download&amp;itm_source=wordstream&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent_links">How to Find Your Target Audience [Simple Steps!]</a></p>
<div id="why-do-you-need-a-target-audience"></div>
<h2>Why you need a target audience</h2>
<p>To avoid targeting everyone and no oneâ€”and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/losing-money-in-google-ads">wasting your budgeted ad spend</a> in the processâ€”you need a target audience.</p>
<p>When the target audience is missing or muddy, itâ€™s obvious. Take this commercial from T Mobile that was somehow a Super Bowl spot in 2024, for example.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/YVeCwSWNLrM?si=riJj2FkPjZW7o3Ri" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" data-mce-fragment="1"></iframe></p>
<p>It is entirely unclear who this is forâ€”Scrubs fans? Musical fans? Aquaman fans? Suburbanites with internet issues and parties to host? As far as I can tell, thereâ€™s no specific customer profile in mind. Thatâ€™s what makes this commercial so frustrating for me. This seems like it was created with a little something for everyone, but by appealing to everyone, youâ€™re often appealing to no one. And this makes your marketing and advertising ineffective.</p>
