</ul>
<h2>6 B2B marketing trends to follow in 2025</h2>
<p>Let these B2B marketing trends guide you as you create your 2025 marketing strategy.</p>
<div id="ai-agents-go-mainstream"></div>
<h3>1. AI agents go mainstream</h3>
<p>AI agents are revolutionizing how everything from a factory floor to a dentist&#8217;s office operates. And they&#8217;re poised to do the same for B2B marketing.</p>
<p>These semi-autonomous problem solvers are already tackling several tasks for marketers, like:</p>
<ul>
<li>Optimizing campaigns</li>
<li>Personalizing marketing messages</li>
<li>Creating content</li>
<li>Improving customer engagements</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-dash-1.webp" alt="B2B marketing trends - Dash screenshot." width="633" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-89026 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-dash-1.webp 633w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-dash-1-480x455.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 633px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>AI agents, like </em><a href="https://localiq.com/products/ai-lead-management/?itm_source=localiq&amp;itm_medium=homepage" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>LocaliQâ€™s Dash</em></a><em>, will help marketers provide more personalized and engaging experiences for prospects and customers.</em></p>
<p>Developers, both big and small, will continue to iterate on how AI agents help marketers. <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/facebook-ad-trends-2025">Facebook</a>, for example, is bringing an AI agent to its <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/facebook-ad-tactics">ads manager</a>. Youâ€™ll just feed it your marketing goals and give it some guidelines, and itâ€™ll deliver the best outcome based on changing factors.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-pechau-1.webp" alt="B2B marketing trends - linkedin post screenshot." width="875" height="549" class="aligncenter wp-image-89027 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-pechau-1.webp 875w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-pechau-1-480x301.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 875px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/chrispechau_breaking-ai-agents-are-coming-to-the-meta-activity-7288182595958284288-7jbN?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>This is probably the fastest-evolving <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-marketing-trends-2025">trend in AI for marketing</a>. If you&#8217;re ready to jump on it, here&#8217;s how to get started.</p>
<h4>Follow thought leaders</h4>
<p>Find a few<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/02/08/ppc-influencers"> marketing thought leaders</a> who talk about AI agents on LinkedIn, in podcasts, and in their<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/02/25/email-newsletter-ideas"> newsletters</a>. Don&#8217;t hesitate to get active in the commentsâ€”you&#8217;ll find many of the best recommendations there.</p>
<h4>List jobs to be done</h4>
<p>AI agents are designed to take on specific tasks. Make a list of workflow bottlenecks and growth opportunities you donâ€™t have the bandwidth to address. Then, look for AI agents that handle them.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4aa.png" alt="ğŸ’ª" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Ready to make 2025 your best marketing year yet?</strong> Get <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/marketing-calendar?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_2025MarketingCalendar_Download&amp;itm_source=wordstream&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent_links">The Only Marketing Calendar You Need for 2025</a> for promotion ideas, tips, social media posts, and more.</p>
<div id="experience-marketing-comes-back-into-focus"></div>
<h3>2. Experience marketing comes back into focus</h3>
<p>Experiential marketing fell out of favor for a while. In large part, that&#8217;s down to marketers focusing on digital mass communication strategies like content and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/social-media-marketing">social media marketing</a>. Of course, the pandemic gave that shift a huge shove, too. But the trend is shifting back now. <a href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/74-fortune-1000-marketers-increase-190000092.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">74%</a> of Fortune 1000 marketers report that theyâ€™ll be increasing spending on experiential marketing in 2025</p>
<p>Almost paradoxically, AI is helping to make experience marking en vogue again for two reasons. First, the specter of robo-crafted content has marketers looking for new ways to connect with audiences more authentically. A conference, webinar, or even sponsored coworking sessions are great ways to do that.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-omahony.webp" alt="B2B marketing trends - linkedin post from a conference." width="571" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-89028 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-omahony.webp 571w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-omahony-480x504.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 571px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/darren-o-mahony-97958225_experiential-marketing-doesnt-just-engageit-activity-7290180737952104450-qVNp?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>At the same time, new <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-tools-for-marketing-agency">AI tools</a> help marketers make more of every event. You can now use AI to pull insights from a keynote speech or expert panel and almost instantly <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/content-repurposing">repurpose</a> it into a series of blog articles, social posts, and video scripts.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-rogers.webp" alt="B2B marketing trends -Linkedin post from mark rogers." width="647" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-89029 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-rogers.webp 647w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-rogers-480x445.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 647px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Some marketing leaders <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/markrogers88_im-adding-a-really-cool-hire-to-the-content-activity-7289999140804018176-NuM2?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop" target="_blank" rel="noopener">are hiring</a> specifically to curate content fodder from marketing events.</em></p>
<p>Events are excellent opportunities to gather first-party data, expert insights, and overall industry trends. Hereâ€™s how you can take advantage of the experiential marketing trend.</p>
<h4>Find ways to host events</h4>
<p>A conference is great, but itâ€™s not in every brandâ€™s budget. Try looking at more manageable events like webinars or even AMA (ask me anything) events on<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/reddit-marketing"> Reddit</a>. You can also get some of the benefits by attending other brandsâ€™ events.</p>
<h4>Get intentional about repurposing</h4>
<p>Before any event you host or attend, create a list of how you can repurpose the information you gather there. When you go in knowing you want five blog articles, three short videos, and a dozen LinkedIn posts, youâ€™ll seek out insights to fill them.</p>
<div id="ai-education-is-now-non-negotiable"></div>
<h3>3. AI education is now non-negotiable</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.surveymonkey.com/mp/ai-marketing-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">More than half</a> of marketers say AI is already important in their role, but 70% said their employers donâ€™t provide generative AI training. In 2025, businesses that create an AI curriculum will close the knowledge gap and be set up for success.</p>
<p>The educational chasm is only going to get deeper. New tools and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-in-marketing">use cases for AI</a> in marketing are increasing exponentially. Wait too long, and the learning curve could get too steep to climb.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-nicole-leffer.webp" alt="B2B marketing trends -Linkedin post from Nicole Leffler." width="936" height="416" class="aligncenter wp-image-89030 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-nicole-leffer.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-nicole-leffer-480x213.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/nicoleleffer_if-youve-been-waiting-for-ai-to-get-easier-activity-7279645459705430016-e-E-/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>Expect to see many more B2B businesses baking in some AI training and experimentation in 2025. The evidence of this marketing trend will be noticeable as thought leaders <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-uses-in-marketing">share their trials</a> and learnings publicly.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-amanda-natividad.webp" alt="B2B marketing trends -Linkedin post from Amanda Natividad." width="936" height="495" class="aligncenter wp-image-89031 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-amanda-natividad.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-amanda-natividad-480x254.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Expect more public </em><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-uses-in-marketing"><em>sharing of AI experiments</em></a><em> and use cases in 2025.</em></p>
<p>AI will only get more entrenched in marketerâ€™s workflows this year. Here are a few ways you and your team can get ahead and stay ahead.</p>
<h4>Formalize your AI education</h4>
<p>Create a structure around you and your teamâ€™s learning activities. Set aside learning time blocks, have experimentation sprints, and dedicate meetings to share new ways to use AI.</p>
<h4>Make use of free tools</h4>
<p>Many new AI tools, like <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/02/25/ai-content-generators">copy generators</a>, offer free versions as a way to gain market penetration. Others offer a â€œfree foreverâ€ plan with limited but still useful features. Use these affordable options to try out new platforms and test use cases.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6d1.png" alt="ğŸ›‘" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Need a little more context about AI?</strong> Download the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/emergency-ai-guide?cid=Web_Any_BlogInContent_PPC_AIMarketing_Download">Emergency Guide to AI in Marketing</a> for a crash course.</p>
<div id="aeo-is-the-new-seo"></div>
<h3>4. AEO is the newest component of SEO</h3>
<p>30-plus years ago, B2B businesses started focusing on getting their websites to appear at the top of Google search pages. Early<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/seo-trends-2025"> SEO tactics</a> were clumsy, rules were ambiguous, and results varied greatly. In 2025, weâ€™ll see B2B marketers take their best shot at answer engine optimization (AEO) so their sites sit atop results in AI platforms like Perplexity and Googleâ€™s Gemini.</p>
<p>AI answer enginesâ€™ place in search is growing. Google expanded its<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ai-overviews"> AI Overviews</a> last year. Perplexityâ€™s user base<a href="https://www.businessofapps.com/data/perplexity-ai-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> continues to increase</a>. And<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/05/chatgpt-seo"> ChatGPT</a> launched its<a href="https://openai.com/index/introducing-chatgpt-search/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> search-focused platform</a>. For each search involving these tools, there are citations to websites that can deliver both<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/07/10/brand-awareness"> brand awareness</a> and clicks from the interaction.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-lily-ray.webp" alt="B2B marketing trends -Linkedin post from Lily Ray." width="503" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-89032 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-lily-ray.webp 503w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-lily-ray-480x573.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 503px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>SEO expert Lily Ray </em><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/lily-ray-44755615_seo-activity-7269046589665538048-K70c?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>pointed out</em></a><em> how many places a brand can be cited in an AI search result.</em></p>
<p>Itâ€™s very likely that weâ€™ll see more online searches involving AI-generated answers. Marketers will follow the search migration and focus more on AEO in 2025. And just like the early days of SEO, those in the know will land more of that coveted citation real estate. Use these tips to get started.</p>
<h4>Get specific in copy and content</h4>
<p>Answer engines seem to like to cite pages with direct answers to specific questions. So, ranking in an AE will be similar to grabbing the coveted feature snippet on a standard Google search. Make sure your copy includes a direct answer to the questions youâ€™re trying to rank for.</p>
<h4>Get your structure down</h4>
<p>FAQs, meta descriptions, and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/09/15/what-is-schema-markup">schema markups</a> will help answer engines understand and share your pages. Go back to those basics if you havenâ€™t already done so.</p>
<h4>Shore up your local listings</h4>
<p>AI search tools pull data for local businesses from <a href="https://localiq.com/products/listings/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">business listings</a>. If your business has a physical location, make sure your <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/holiday-local-listings-checklist/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">directory listings are complete</a> and up to date.</p>
<div id="employee-ambassadors-take-the-lead"></div>
<h3>5. Employee ambassadors take the lead</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/seo">SEO</a> is most certainly not dead, but it does look a lot different than it did just a few years ago. Google SERPs are now rowdy places with frequently violent shifts in rankings and rules. In 2025, weâ€™ll see many B2B marketers respond by diversifying their traffic sources. One popular way to do this is to help their employees become brand ambassadors.</p>
<p>Employee brand ambassadors work a lot like <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/03/21/social-media-influencers">traditional influencers</a>, but theyâ€™re employed by the business theyâ€™re promoting. Theyâ€™ve been popular in B2C marketing for a while (this <a href="https://www.tiktok.com/@bartoli" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Papa Johnâ€™s pizza maker</a> has 1.4 million TikTok followers).</p>
<p>Scroll through LinkedIn, and youâ€™ll see how the trend is taking over in the B2B space as well.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-nielson-1.webp" alt="B2B marketing trends -Linkedin post from Amanda Nielson." width="344" height="578" class="aligncenter wp-image-89033 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-nielson-1.webp 344w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-nielson-1-179x300.webp 179w" sizes="(max-width: 344px) 100vw, 344px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Employee brand ambassadors are bringing the </em><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/verydemanda_adhd-hack-power-walk-on-your-treadmill-during-activity-7282129975061716992-B-jJ?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>TikTok vibe to LinkedIn</em></a><em>.</em></p>
<p>There will be many variations on the internal influencer theme. Many will be marketers whose job it is to promote the brand online. But youâ€™ll also see more engineers, customer success reps, and sales pros amplify their businessâ€™s digital footprint.</p>
<p>Keep these ideas handy as you consider joining this B2B marketing trend.</p>
<h4>Offer a variety of ways to participate</h4>
<p>Not everyone in your office (virtual or otherwise) will be eager to post <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/tiktok-video-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TikTok-like videos</a> or create extensive product demos for LinkedIn. And you donâ€™t need them to. Start by asking them to repost a post or shout out a milestone on their account. Give them the option to jump in doing whatever feels natural and build from there.</p>
<h4>Give them tools and incentives</h4>
<p>Unless they were hired as an influencer, youâ€™re asking something extra from someone who may not be familiar with <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/01/09/social-media-marketing-strategies">social media marketing best practices</a>. As you create your employee brand ambassador program, include some incentives (like helping them build their personal brand) and support (like writing captions for them).</p>
<div id="ai-transparency-becomes-a-big-debate"></div>
<h3>6. AI transparency becomes a big debate</h3>
<p>While many people donâ€™t care if robots created your marketing copy, most want you to tell them if it was. In two recent surveys,<a href="https://www.telusdigital.com/insights/ai-data/article/generative-ai-transparency" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> 71%</a> and<a href="https://www.bynder.com/en/blog/bynders-human-touch-survey-uncovers-consumers-opinions/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> 69%</a> of respondents said that businesses should say when they use AI. Another poll by the AI Policy Institute showed that<a href="https://nz.news.yahoo.com/80-percent-americans-think-presenting-100042782.html?guccounter=1&amp;guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucmVkZGl0LmNvbS8&amp;guce_referrer_sig=AQAAAMUqxLsFl6ObVWeYbGRQs4HIT1_gn2V3jEvIg8lsBaFosbN-MtrPUZnA7R6JV_9b7tMl1kzU1Dcn4AB36B8jhATmV8gwfmvFUfytLhZDRWboebj_qKhWK66B4AwL7yYTAsqhIGEwJxO0MnJKS5IftAkC02p-9iIKykZSIOgXQZuy" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> 80%</a> of Americans think it should be illegal to pass off AI-generated content as created by humans.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-ai-images.webp" alt="B2B marketing trends -AI-generated image." width="936" height="474" class="aligncenter wp-image-89034 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-ai-images.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/b2b-marketing-trends-wordstream-ai-images-480x243.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/best-ai-photo-generators"><em>AI photo generators</em></a><em> are getting really good, making it hard for the average consumer to know whatâ€™s real and whatâ€™s AI.</em></p>
<p>Weâ€™ll also see new federal, state, and industry <a href="https://www.akingump.com/en/insights/ai-law-and-regulation-tracker/new-hampshire-imposes-new-regulations-on-ai-and-criminalizes-deepfakes" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AI regulations</a> add energy to the need for transparency.</p>
<p>The exact way B2B marketers react is still unknown. We may see brands self-regulate by adding disclosures about their AI use. Or we may get vertical best practices from individual industries (like healthcare, for example).</p>
<p>No matter what it looks like, 2025 will be the year transparency becomes a big part of the AI transformation. Here are some ways to be prepared.</p>
<h4>Create an internal AI use policy</h4>
<p>The most important step in planning for AI is codifying how your team should use it (and how they should discuss it). Itâ€™s okay to start simply with rules around writing blog posts and creating images. Remember to consider privacy since many AI models use the information you give them as a part of their training protocol.</p>
<h4>Consider an AI use statement</h4>
<p>If you want to get ahead of industry or legal standards, consider adding an AI use statement to your website. Explain how you use AI for asset creation, customer data, or other purposes.</p>
<h2>Map your success with these B2B marketing trends</h2>
<p>Few aspects of B2B marketing escaped the sudden shifts over the last couple of years. If you&#8217;re feeling a little dizzy from it all, know you&#8217;re not alone and that there&#8217;s a path to success. The most important step is to stay informed. Find a few information sources you enjoy, try some <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/bluesky-for-marketing">new social media platforms</a>, and dedicate time to learning it all.</p>
<p>The B2B marketing trends we&#8217;ve listed here are a good place to start. Here&#8217;s a handy recap:</p>
<ol>
<li>AI agents go mainstream</li>
<li>Experience marketing comes back into focus</li>
<li>AI education is now non-negotiable</li>
<li>AEO is the newest component of SEO</li>
<li>Employee ambassadors take the lead</li>
<li>AI transparency becomes a big debate</li>
</ol>
