										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Anyone can set goals. But sticking to them and actually achieving them? Well, thatâ€™s a whole different ball game.</p>
<p>Between procrastination, reprioritization, changes in your organization, or maybe even brain-on-vacation, there are a million things that get in the way of you, your team, or our business achieving your goals.</p>
<p>But not if youâ€™re armed with SMART goals. In this article, weâ€™re going to cover what SMART goals are and then share 11 examples you can model after.</p>
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#what-are-smart-goals">What are SMART goals?</a></li>
<li><a href="#smart-goal-examples-for-marketing">SMART goal examples for marketing</a></li>
<li><a href="#smart-goal-examples-for-work-and-business">SMART goal examples for businesses</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="what-are-smart-goals"></div>
<h2>What are SMART goals?</h2>
<p>SMART goals are<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/06/15/marketing-objectives"> objectives</a> that have a clear structure to them. Theyâ€™re the goals you will enjoy setting and your boss will appreciate seeing. Best of all, with this framework, youâ€™ll be equipped to achieve them.</p>
<p>SMART stands for:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Specific</strong>: Clear and detailed to eliminate ambiguity and provide direction.</li>
<li><strong>Measurable: </strong>You need a way to track progress and determine success.</li>
<li><strong>Achievable:</strong> Your goals need to be realistic, given your bandwidth.</li>
<li><strong>Relevant:</strong> Aligned with your broader objectives and <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/long-term-business-goals-with-examples/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">long-term business goals</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Time-bound:</strong> Have a deadline or time frame to encourage accountability.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-smart-chart-1-1.webp" alt="smart goals examples - chart showing SMART components." width="849" height="434" class="aligncenter wp-image-88263 size-full" /></p>
<p>Letâ€™s take a look at some examples.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f3af.png" alt="ğŸ¯" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><strong> Ready to achieve the goals youâ€™ve just set?</strong> This list of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/online-marketing-tips?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_130marketingtips_Download">130+ of the Best Online Marketing Tips for Generating More Traffic, Leads, &amp; Sales</a> will help.</p>
<div id="smart-goal-examples-for-marketing"></div>
<h2>SMART goal examples for marketing</h2>
<p>Letâ€™s start with some examples of SMART goals for marketing.</p>
<h3>1. Increase website traffic by 20%</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/08/14/increase-traffic-to-my-website">Increasing website traffic</a> is a common goal for many businesses. Hereâ€™s how to make it SMART:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Specific: </strong>Increase website traffic through targeted <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/seo-content-beginners-guide">SEO content</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Measurable:</strong> Increase by 20% (from 5,000 to 6,000 monthly visitors).</li>
<li><strong>Achievable: </strong>Use <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/keywords">keyword research tools</a> and publish two SEO-optimized blog posts per week.</li>
<li><strong>Relevant: </strong>More traffic will result in higher <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/lead-generation-ideas">lead generation</a> and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/07/10/brand-awareness">brand visibility</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Time-bound: </strong>Achieve this goal within the next three months.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-SEO-content.webp" alt="smart goals examples - screenshot of an SEO blog post." width="416" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-88264 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-SEO-content.webp 416w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-SEO-content-208x300.webp 208w" sizes="(max-width: 416px) 100vw, 416px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Track each piece of SEO content to see which helps you achieve your traffic goals.</em></p>
<h3>2. Increase social media engagement by 10%</h3>
<p>No better way to improve your <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/best-social-media-marketing-strategies-for-smb/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">social media marketing strategy</a> than with some measurable goals. For example:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Specific: </strong><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/09/27/how-to-increase-instagram-engagement">Increase Instagram engagement</a> rate by 10% with <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/02/13/ugc-instagram">user-generated content</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Measurable: </strong>Achieve a 10% engagement rate (up from 7%) and gain 500 new followers.</li>
<li><strong>Achievable: </strong>Run two monthly campaigns featuring <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/04/28/user-generated-content">user-generated content</a>. Use existing design tools and encourage followers to participate with contests.</li>
<li><strong>Relevant: </strong>Strong social engagement fosters brand awareness, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/brand-loyalty">brand loyalty</a>, and trust.</li>
<li><strong>Time-bound: </strong>Reach these metrics by the end of the next quarter.</li>
</ul>
<p>Learn more about creating a SMART <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/social-media-strategy">social media strategy here,</a></p>
<h3>3. Generate 50 sales-qualified leads per month</h3>
<p>If email plays a role in your <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/marketing-objectives-examples/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">marketing objectives</a> (and it very well should), hereâ€™s an example SMART goal to model after:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Specific: </strong>Generate 50 sales-qualified leads each month through a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2016/05/13/targeted-email-marketing-strategies">segmented email</a> campaign.</li>
<li><strong>Measurable:</strong> Generate 50 sales-qualified leads each month. Track performance through click-through rates (CTR) and lead form submissions.</li>
<li><strong>Achievable: </strong>Leverage an email list of 5,000 contacts and create compelling ebooks to use as <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/08/18/gated-content">gated content</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Relevant: </strong>High-quality leads will improve conversion rates and revenue.</li>
<li><strong>Time-bound: </strong>Maintain this pace consistently for the next six months.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-segmented-email.webp" alt="smart goals examples - segmented email example." width="636" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-88265 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-segmented-email.webp 636w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-segmented-email-480x453.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 636px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Segmenting your email list is a common lead-generation strategy.</em></p>
<p><strong><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/2b50.png" alt="â­" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Free lead-generating asset!</strong> <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDL25LeadGenIdeas.html?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_LeadGenIdeas_Download">The Definitive Guide to Lead Generation: 25 Ideas (+Tips &amp; Examples)</a>.</p>
<h3>4. Reduce Google Ads CPL by 25%</h3>
<p>There are tons of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/10/19/ppc-metrics">PPC metrics</a> to target with SMART goals. Hereâ€™s an example for <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/11/07/how-to-lower-cost-per-lead-google-ads">lowering the cost per (CPL) lead in Google Ads</a>:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Specific</strong>: Reduce Google Ads CPL by 25% by optimizing <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/facebook-ad-targeting">ad targeting</a> and keywords.</li>
<li><strong>Measurable</strong>: Lower CPL from $40 to $30.</li>
<li><strong>Achievable</strong>: Use A/B testing on ad creatives and refine <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/08/04/customer-segmentation-models">audience segmentation</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Relevant</strong>: Improved ROI will directly impact marketing profitability.</li>
<li><strong>Time-bound:</strong> Reach this target within the next 4 months.</li>
</ul>
<h3>5. Improve online rating from 4.2 to 4.5</h3>
<ol start="5"></ol>
<ul>
<li><strong>Specific:</strong> Improve <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/06/27/google-my-business">Google Business Profile</a> rating from 4.2 to 4.5 by encouraging 20 satisfied customers to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/09/16/get-more-google-reviews">leave reviews</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Measurable:</strong> Aim for 20 new 5-star reviews.</li>
<li><strong>Achievable:</strong> Implement an automated email for customers who give an NPS of 8 or higher.</li>
<li><strong>Relevant:</strong> A strong online reputation will attract more local customers.</li>
<li><strong>Time-bound:</strong> Achieve this within one month.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-reviews.webp" alt="smart goals examples - screenshot of customer review capture on a website." width="888" height="577" class="aligncenter wp-image-88266 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-reviews.webp 888w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-reviews-480x312.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 888px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>You can add a link in your website to encourage more customer reviews.</em></p>
<div id="smart-goal-examples-for-work-and-business"></div>
<h2>More SMART goal examples for work and business</h2>
<p>You can use SMART goals for more than just <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/performance-marketing">performance marketing</a>. Here are some more SMART goal examples for other areas of business growth.</p>
<h3>6. Increase monthly revenue by 20%</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Specific</strong>: Increase monthly revenue by 20% by improving <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/05/30/cross-selling-upselling">upselling strategies</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Measurable</strong>: Increase revenue by 20%, aiming for five upsells a month.</li>
<li><strong>Achievable</strong>: Use <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/07/21/promotional-email-examples">targeted email</a> and call campaigns from account executives to reach this goal.</li>
<li><strong>Relevant</strong>: Supports overall business growth objectives.</li>
<li><strong>Time-Bound</strong>: Achieve this by the end of the next fiscal quarter.</li>
</ul>
<h3>7. Improve customer retention rate by 15%</h3>
<ol start="7"></ol>
<ul>
<li><strong>Specific</strong>: Improve <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/03/09/customer-retention-strategies">customer retention</a> rate by 15% through <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/07/18/loyalty-marketing">loyalty programs</a> and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/02/06/personalized-marketing">personalized email campaigns</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Measurable</strong>: Improve by 15%. Measure retention through repeat purchase rates and churn data.</li>
<li><strong>Achievable</strong>: Train the support team and implement a customer feedback system. Promote a loyalty program through email campaigns.</li>
<li><strong>Relevant</strong>: Addresses the need to maintain a loyal customer base and increase customer long-term value (LTV).</li>
<li><strong>Time-bound</strong>: Complete initiatives within six months.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-loyalty.webp" alt="smart goals examples - screenshot of a loyalty program chart. " width="603" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-88267 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-loyalty.webp 603w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-loyalty-480x478.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 603px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Many brands use loyalty programs to increase customer retention.</em></p>
<h3>8. Improve team productivity by 10%</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Specific</strong>: Reduce project completion time by 10%.</li>
<li><strong>Measurable</strong>: Monitor average project completion times and aim to complete them 10% faster.</li>
<li><strong>Achievable</strong>: Introduce a project management tool like Asana or Trello. Conduct team training and document standardized processes.</li>
<li><strong>Relevant</strong>: Helps meet deadlines, improve efficiency, and improve customer satisfaction.</li>
<li><strong>Time-bound</strong>: Implement changes and track results within three months.</li>
</ul>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="ğŸ’¡" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><strong> Use SMART goals to achieve an <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/always-on-marketing?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_alwaysonmarketing_Download&amp;itm_source=localiq&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent_links" target="_blank" rel="noopener">always-on marketing strategy</a> </strong>with this free guide!</p>
<h3>9. Expand market reach</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Specific</strong>: Enter three new local markets by the end of the year.</li>
<li><strong>Measurable</strong>: Enter three new markets. Measure success by market penetration rates and sales data. Obtain at least five <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/07/16/how-to-ask-for-reviews">new Google reviews</a> in each new market.</li>
<li><strong>Achievable</strong>: Allocate budget and resources for market entry. Create<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/12/15/local-marketing-ideas"> localized marketing campaigns</a>, partner with local distributors, and run <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/grand-opening-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">grand opening</a> specials for each market.</li>
<li><strong>Relevant</strong>: Tied to the goal of business expansion.</li>
<li><strong>Time-Bound</strong>: Achieve this by the end of the year.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-grand-opening.webp" alt="smart goals examples - Ad for a soft launch." width="619" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-88268 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-grand-opening.webp 619w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-grand-opening-480x465.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 619px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Cross-marketing on a variety of channels is an important part of expanding into new markets.</em></p>
<h3>10. Improve customer service</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Specific</strong>: Achieve a 90% customer satisfaction rate by reducing response times and enhancing training for support representatives.</li>
<li><strong>Measurable</strong>: 90% satisfaction rate, tracked through surveys and reviews. Reduce response times to five minutes or less, tracked through an internal ticketing system.</li>
<li><strong>Achievable</strong>: Deploy <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/02/13/chatbot-examples">chatbots</a> and increase live agent availability. Conduct training sessions and offer incentives for performance improvement.</li>
<li><strong>Relevant</strong>: Aligns with a customer-centric strategy.</li>
<li><strong>Time-Bound</strong>: Meet the goal within six months.</li>
</ul>
<h3>11. Launch a new product</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Specific</strong>: Successfully <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/07/29/how-to-promote-a-product">launch a new product</a> by finalizing development, creating a go-to-market strategy, and onboarding 1,000 new customers.</li>
<li><strong>Measurable</strong>: Measure success through pre-orders, sales, and customer feedback.</li>
<li><strong>Achievable</strong>: Allocate cross-functional teams and a realistic budget.</li>
<li><strong>Relevant</strong>: Expands the product portfolio and diversifies revenue streams.</li>
<li><strong>Time-Bound</strong>: Launch within the next eight months.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Get started with these SMART goal examples</h2>
<p>Goals without SMART characteristics are no more than daydreams in disguise. So whether you&#8217;re aiming to generate leads, boost revenue, engage customers, or something (anything) else, SMART is the way to go. This framework gives you a clear map to follow. Best of all, you will get the gratification of achieving those goals!</p>
